reviewText: This is a good, solid spy caper featuring a good, solid Tyrone Power in a more adult role than when he was being used by Daryl Zanuck as his answer to Errol Flynn.  Power showed he could act in "The Razor's Edge" and "Nightmare Alley".  This is a good vehicle to expand his dramatic chops in.  Not a great film but a very enjoyable one with fast pacing and a good cast.  If you like Power or even remember him this is a good example of what he could bring to the screen.
